IUC 1: Ek int array me se average print karo.

int[] arr = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
int sum = 0;
for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
    sum += arr[i];
}
double avg = (double)sum/arr.length;
System.out.println(avg);

IUC 2:
Ek number ka factorial print karo (number = 5).

int n = 5;
int fact = 1;
for(int i=1; i<=n; i++){
    fact *= i;
}
System.out.println(fact);

IUC 3:
Ek int array ko reverse order me print karo.

int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
for(int i=arr.length-1; i>=0; i--){
    System.out.println(arr[i]);
}

IUC 4:
Ek int array me kitne even numbers hain woh count karo.

int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6};
int count = 0;
for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
    if(arr[i] % 2 == 0){
        count++;
    }
}
System.out.println(count);

IUC 5: Ek int array me har element ka square print karo.

int[] arr = {2, 3, 4, 5};
for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
    System.out.println(arr[i]*arr[i]);
}
